        <blockquote>"We are the original people — Onkwehonwe — and Turtle Island belongs to all of us."</blockquote>
        <p>The Kanien'kehá:ka — People of the Flint — are one of the original nations of the Haudenosaunee Confederacy, a sophisticated democratic union established centuries before European contact. We are the Keepers of the Eastern Door.</p>
        <p>The Turtle Clan is one of three Mohawk clans, alongside Wolf and Bear. The turtle represents patience, wisdom, and endurance — carrying the world on its back. Clan identity passes through the mother, connecting every generation to the earth and to one another.</p>
        <p>Kahnawà:ke, south of Montreal, is home to a thriving Mohawk community that has maintained its sovereignty, language, and traditions while also building bridges to the modern world — on both sides of an arbitrary border.</p>

