<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════
     CULTURE
══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="culture">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow reveal">
      <span class="section-label">Living Culture</span>
    </div>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">What We Carry Forward</h2>
    <p class="section-body reveal reveal-delay-1" style="margin-bottom:3rem">Mohawk culture is not a relic — it is alive, practiced, spoken, and passed down. These are some of the pillars of Kanien'kehá:ka identity that we carry forward into every generation.</p>

    <div class="culture-grid">

      <div class="culture-item reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <span class="culture-num">01</span>
        <div class="culture-icon">
          <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 36 36" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path d="M18,4 C18,4 10,10 10,20 C10,28 14,32 18,32 C22,32 26,28 26,20 C26,10 18,4 18,4Z" fill="none" stroke="#F2C84B" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <path d="M18,10 C18,10 13,15 13,22 C13,27 15.5,30 18,30" fill="none" stroke="#E8931A" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.7"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="culture-title">Kanien'kéha — The Language</div>
        <p class="culture-text">The Mohawk language is a living connection to thousands of years of knowledge. Language revitalization efforts at Kahnawà:ke and other communities are bringing Kanien'kéha back into daily life, schools, and homes. Language is sovereignty.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="culture-item reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <span class="culture-num">02</span>
        <div class="culture-icon">
          <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 36 36" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <circle cx="18" cy="18" r="12" fill="none" stroke="#E8931A" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <circle cx="18" cy="18" r="6" fill="none" stroke="#F2C84B" stroke-width="1"/>
            <line x1="18" y1="6"  x2="18" y2="30" stroke="#F2C84B" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5"/>
            <line x1="6"  y1="18" x2="30" y2="18" stroke="#F2C84B" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="culture-title">Clan System & Governance</div>
        <p class="culture-text">The Turtle, Wolf, and Bear clans form the social and political backbone of Mohawk society. Clan mothers hold the power to appoint and remove chiefs. This matrilineal system predates any modern democracy and continues to guide our self-governance today.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="culture-item reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <span class="culture-num">03</span>
        <div class="culture-icon">
          <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 36 36" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <rect x="4" y="4" width="8" height="8" fill="#6B4C8A"/>
