        <div class="culture-title">Ironwork & Sovereignty in Action</div>
        <p class="culture-text">Mohawks from Kahnawà:ke became legendary high-steel ironworkers, building skylines across New York and beyond — a tradition dating to the 1880s Lachine Bridge construction. This is Mohawk ingenuity and fearlessness made visible in the modern world.</p>
